<taxonomicName authorityName="Jocque &amp; Baert" authorityYear="2005" box="[439,589,1655,1681]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Epicratinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pugionifer">
<emphasis box="[439,589,1655,1681]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">E. pugionifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are easily recognized by the long RTA spear-shaped, reaching almost half of the cymbium, and this one with a deep concavity accommodating it. Females have a large oval atrium with a conspicuous anterior border and inconspicuous lateral border in a potion near the spermathecae (
<figureCitation box="[1233,1320,1725,1752]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1916,1940]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,725,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-201@26.[340,1247,724,1893]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 12. Epicratinus pugionifer. A. (UFMG 7757) Habitus male, dorsal view. B. Male, ventral view. C. (MPEG 003532) Female, dorsal view. D. Female, ventral view. (Scale = 2 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4297359" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4297359/files/figure.png" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Figs 12</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1332,1363,1726,1752]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1016,1040]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,181,993]" captionTargetId="figure-19@27.[340,1247,181,993]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 13. Epicratinus pugionifer.A. (UFMG 7757) Male palp, dorsal view. B. (UFMG 7757) and C. (UFMG 5719) Ventral view. D. (MPEG 003532) Epigynum, ventral view. E. (MPEG 003531) Vulva. C: conductor; E: embolus; St: subtegulum; T: tegulum. (Scale in A, B, C = 0.5; D = 0.2; E = 1 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4297361" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4297361/files/figure.png" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">13</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
